<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<TestCaseEntity>
   <description>As an ER Sr. Coder I want to access the Respond tab on the Escalation Case screen so that I can view the task I want to resolve. 

Acceptance Criteria: 

RM-1510.1: CDAT provides a View Submission option for the user to view medical record documentation. 

RM-1510.2: CDAT provides an Open Encoder Tool option for Focused Review and Discrepant Confirmation ER Senior Coders to open the Encoder Tool for research purposes only. 

RM-1510.3: CDAT provides the following options on the Respond tab: 
•View Submission - allows the user to view the submitted coversheet, attestation, if applicable and medical record) 
•Exit - returns user to the Open tab on the Escalation Senior Coder queue 
• Escalate to QA Panel - sends the task to the QA Panel 
•Save - saves the user's work 
•Send Response - saves and submits the task to back to the user who escalated the case. 

RM-1510.4: The Respond tab displays the following header information: 
•Escalation Case ID 
•Coversheet ID 
•Escalation Submitted By: (username) 
•Step (the step from which the escalation was made) 
•Date Escalated 

RM-1510.5: CDAT displays the escalation comment as read only in the Respond tab.</description>
